{
  "bio": [
    "Bernard Lewis founded UK-based clothing retailer River Island Fashion in 1948; it now sells online and has stores in several European countries.",
    "The business had revenues in 2022 of over $900 million.",
    "His nephew Ben Lewis, who started as a store manager in 1990, serves as CEO.",
    "Lewis and his family are also investors in property development and private equity across UK, Europe, US, Caribbean and Thailand."
  ],
  "about": [
    "Lewis launched his entrepreneurial career at age 20 by establishing a fruit & vegetable stall in a makeshift shack constructed on a bombsite in North London in 1946.",
    "In 2025, River Island faced severe financial pressures, prompting a restructuring plan to avert bankruptcy."
  ]
}